  "local_port": 55676,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My viber on PC doesnt connect to internet. whats the problem? It shows me the messages that other send me but I cant reply through my pc.",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear you're experiencing issues with Viber on your PC. Let's work through some troubleshooting steps to identify and resolve the problem:\n\n### 1. **Check Your Internet Connection**\n- **Ensure Stability:** Verify that your PC has a stable internet connection. Try browsing websites or using other online applications to confirm connectivity.\n- **Speed Test:** Sometimes, slow internet speeds can affect app performance. You can use online tools like [Speedtest](https://www.speedtest.net/) to check your connection speed.\n\n### 2. **Verify Viber\u2019s Server Status**\n- **Viber Status Page:** Occasionally, Viber's servers may experience downtime. Check [Viber's official Twitter account](https://twitter.com/viber) or websites like [Downdetector](https://downdetector.com/status/viber/) to see if others are reporting similar issues.\n\n### 3. **Restart Viber and Your PC**\n- **Restart Viber:** Completely close the Viber application. On Windows, you can ensure it's closed by checking the Task Manager (`Ctrl + Shift + Esc`) and ending any Viber processes.\n- **Restart Your PC:** Sometimes, a simple reboot can resolve temporary glitches.\n\n### 4. **Update Viber to the Latest Version**\n- **Check for Updates:**\n  - Open Viber on your PC.\n  - Click on the **Menu** (three horizontal lines) in the top-left corner.\n  - Go to **Help** > **Check for Updates**.\n- **Download Latest Version:** If an update is available, follow the prompts to install it. Alternatively, you can [download the latest version from Viber\u2019s official website](https://www.viber.com/en/download/).\n\n### 5. **Re-establish the Connection Between Your Phone and PC**\nViber for PC syncs with your mobile device. Ensure that:\n- **Phone Connection:** Your smartphone is connected to the internet (Wi-Fi or mobile data) and is nearby.\n- **Sync Status:** Open Viber on your phone, go to **More** > **Settings** > **Viber Web/Desktop** to check the connection status. If needed, reconnect by scanning the QR code displayed on your PC\u2019s Viber app.\n\n### 6. **Check Firewall and Antivirus Settings**\nSometimes, security software can block Viber\u2019s access to the internet.\n- **Windows Firewall:**\n  - Go to **Control Panel** > **System and Security** > **Windows Defender Firewall** > **Allow an app or feature through Windows Defender Firewall**.\n  - Ensure that Viber is allowed on both **Private** and **Public** networks.\n- **Antivirus Software:** If you're using third-party antivirus software, check its settings to ensure Viber isn't being blocked. You may need to add Viber to the list of allowed applications.\n\n### 7. **Disable VPN or Proxy (If Applicable)**\n- **VPN Services:** If you're using a VPN, try disabling it temporarily to see if Viber connects properly.\n- **Proxy Settings:** Ensure that proxy settings aren\u2019t interfering with Viber's ability to connect. You can check proxy settings in your browser or system settings.\n\n### 8. **Reinstall Viber**\n- **Uninstall Viber:**\n  - Go to **Settings** > **Apps** (or **Control Panel** > **Programs and Features** on older Windows versions).\n  - Find Viber in the list, select it, and choose **Uninstall**.\n- **Delete Residual Files:**\n  - After uninstalling, navigate to `C:\\Users\\[Your Username]\\AppData\\Local\\Viber` and delete any remaining Viber folders to ensure a clean installation.\n- **Reinstall Viber:**\n  - Download the latest version from the [official Viber website](https://www.viber.com/en/download/) and install it on your PC.\n- **Reconnect Your Account:** Open Viber and follow the prompts to link your account with your mobile device again.\n\n### 9. **Ensure Your Mobile Device\u2019s Viber is Functioning Properly**\n- **Functionality Check:** Ensure that Viber on your smartphone is working correctly, as issues on your phone can affect the PC app.\n- **Update Mobile Viber:** Make sure the Viber app on your phone is updated to the latest version available in the App Store or Google Play Store.\n\n### 10. **Contact Viber Support**\nIf you've tried all the above steps and still can't send messages from your PC:\n- **Viber Support Page:** Visit the [Viber Help Center](https://help.viber.com/) for additional resources.\n- **Submit a Request:** You can contact Viber support directly by submitting a request through their [contact form](https://help.viber.com/en/contact-us).\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Check for Multiple Sessions:** If you're logged into Viber on multiple devices, try logging out from all devices and then reconnect only on your PC to see if that resolves the issue.\n- **Operating System Updates:** Ensure your PC's operating system is up-to-date, as some updates can fix compatibility issues.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to identify and resolve the issue preventing you from replying to messages on Viber for PC. If the problem persists after trying all the suggestions, reaching out to Viber\u2019s support team would be the best course of action.",
